#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn22.100"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.100:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.100:0.2"
msgid "10. Pupphavagga "
msgstr "10. Flowers "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.100:0.3"
msgid "100. Dutiyagaddulabaddhasutta "
msgstr "100. A Leash (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.151, sc1
msgctxt "sn22.100:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.100:1.2"
msgid "“Anamataggoyaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃsāro. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, transmigration has no known beginning. "

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.3"
msgid "Pubbā koṭi na paññāyati avijjānīvaraṇānaṃ sattānaṃ taṇhāsaṃyojanānaṃ sandhāvataṃ saṃsarataṃ. "
msgstr "No first point is found of sentient beings roaming and transmigrating, hindered by ignorance and fettered by craving. "

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, sā gaddulabaddho daḷhe khīle vā thambhe vā upanibaddho. So gacchati cepi tameva khīlaṃ vā thambhaṃ vā upagacchati; tiṭṭhati cepi tameva khīlaṃ vā thambhaṃ vā upatiṭṭhati; nisīdati cepi tameva khīlaṃ vā thambhaṃ vā upanisīdati; nipajjati cepi tameva khīlaṃ vā thambhaṃ vā upanipajjati. "
msgstr "Suppose a dog on a leash was tethered to a strong post or pillar. Whether walking, standing, sitting, or lying down, it stays right beside that post or pillar. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.100:1.5"
msgid "Evameva kho, bhikkhave, assutavā puthujjano rūpaṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati. "
msgstr "In the same way, an uneducated ordinary person regards form like this: ‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self.’ "

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.6"
msgid "Vedanaṃ … "
msgstr "They regard feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.7"
msgid "saññaṃ … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.8"
msgid "saṅkhāre … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.9"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassati. "
msgstr "consciousness like this: ‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self.’ "

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.10"
msgid "So gacchati cepi ime pañcupādānakkhandhe upagacchati; "
msgstr "When walking, they walk right beside the five grasping aggregates. "

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.11"
msgid "tiṭṭhati cepi ime pañcupādānakkhandhe upatiṭṭhati; "
msgstr "When standing … "

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.12"
msgid "nisīdati cepi ime pañcupādānakkhandhe upanisīdati; "
msgstr "sitting … "

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.13"
msgid "nipajjati cepi ime pañcupādānakkhandhe upanipajjati. "
msgstr "lying down, they lie down right beside the five grasping aggregates. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.100:1.14"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, abhikkhaṇaṃ sakaṃ cittaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ: "
msgstr "So you should regularly check your own mind: "

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.15"
msgid "‘dīgharattamidaṃ cittaṃ saṅkiliṭṭhaṃ rāgena dosena mohenā’ti. "
msgstr "‘For a long time this mind has been corrupted by greed, hate, and delusion.’ "

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.16"
msgid "Cittasaṅkilesā, bhikkhave, sattā saṅkilissanti; "
msgstr "Sentient beings are corrupted because the mind is corrupted. "

msgctxt "sn22.100:1.17"
msgid "cittavodānā sattā visujjhanti. "
msgstr "Sentient beings are purified because the mind is purified. "

# NOTE: See BB’s note for the name of the picture. The commentarial explanation is hardly plausible. Surely the picture must, like very many illustrations in the ancient world, be a pedagogic device, where various kinds of conduct are depicted, perhaps with their results.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn22.100:2.1"
msgid "Diṭṭhaṃ vo, bhikkhave, caraṇaṃ nāma cittan”ti? "
msgstr "Mendicants, have you seen the picture called ‘Conduct’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.100:2.2"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

# NOTE: It is of course impossible to capture in English the pun here between citta = mind and citta = colorful.
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.100:2.3"
msgid "“Tampi kho, bhikkhave, caraṇaṃ nāma cittaṃ citteneva cittitaṃ. Tenapi kho, bhikkhave, caraṇena cittena cittaññeva cittataraṃ. "
msgstr "“That picture was elaborated by the mind, but the mind is even more elaborate than that. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.100:2.4"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, abhikkhaṇaṃ sakaṃ cittaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ: "
msgstr "So you should regularly check your own mind: "

msgctxt "sn22.100:2.5"
msgid "‘dīgharattamidaṃ cittaṃ saṅkiliṭṭhaṃ rāgena dosena mohenā’ti. "
msgstr "‘For a long time this mind has been corrupted by greed, hate, and delusion.’ "

msgctxt "sn22.100:2.6"
msgid "Cittasaṅkilesā, bhikkhave, sattā saṅkilissanti; "
msgstr "Sentient beings are corrupted because the mind is corrupted. "

msgctxt "sn22.100:2.7"
msgid "cittavodānā sattā visujjhanti. "
msgstr "Sentient beings are purified because the mind is purified. "

# NOTE: MS punctuation is wrong, I have corrected it.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.152, sc3
msgctxt "sn22.100:3.1"
msgid "Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, aññaṃ ekanikāyampi samanupassāmi evaṃ cittaṃ yathayidaṃ, bhikkhave, tiracchānagatā pāṇā. "
msgstr "I don’t see see any other order of beings as elaborate as the animal realm. "

msgctxt "sn22.100:3.2"
msgid "tepi kho, bhikkhave, tiracchānagatā pāṇā citteneva cittitā, tehipi kho, bhikkhave, tiracchānagatehi pāṇehi cittaññeva cittataraṃ. "
msgstr "The creatures in the animal realm were elaborated by the mind, but the mind is even more elaborate than that. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.100:3.3"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, abhikkhaṇaṃ sakaṃ cittaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ: "
msgstr "So you should regularly check your own mind: "

msgctxt "sn22.100:3.4"
msgid "‘dīgharattamidaṃ cittaṃ saṅkiliṭṭhaṃ rāgena dosena mohenā’ti. "
msgstr "‘For a long time this mind has been corrupted by greed, hate, and delusion.’ "

msgctxt "sn22.100:3.5"
msgid "Cittasaṅkilesā, bhikkhave, sattā saṅkilissanti; "
msgstr "Sentient beings are corrupted because the mind is corrupted. "

msgctxt "sn22.100:3.6"
msgid "cittavodānā sattā visujjhanti. "
msgstr "Sentient beings are purified because the mind is purified. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
#. VAR: mañjiṭṭhāya → mañjeṭṭhāya (bj, s1-3, km) | mañjeṭṭhiyā (pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.100:4.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, rajako vā cittakārako vā rajanāya vā lākhāya vā haliddiyā vā nīliyā vā mañjiṭṭhāya vā suparimaṭṭhe phalake vā bhittiyā vā dussapaṭṭe vā itthirūpaṃ vā purisarūpaṃ vā abhinimmineyya sabbaṅgapaccaṅgiṃ; "
msgstr "Suppose an artist or painter had some dye, red lac, turmeric, indigo, or rose madder. And on a polished plank or a wall or a canvas they’d create the image of a woman or a man, complete in all its various parts. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.100:4.2"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, assutavā puthujjano rūpaññeva abhinibbattento abhinibbatteti, vedanaññeva … pe … saññaññeva … saṅkhāreyeva … viññāṇaññeva abhinibbattento abhinibbatteti. "
msgstr "In the same way, when an uneducated ordinary person creates a future life, all they create is form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.100:4.3"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn22.100:4.4"
msgid "rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "Is form permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.100:4.5"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.100:4.6"
msgid "“Vedanā … "
msgstr "“Is feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.100:4.7"
msgid "saññā … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.100:4.8"
msgid "saṅkhārā … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.100:4.9"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "consciousness permanent or impermanent?” … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.100:4.10"
msgid "“tasmātiha, bhikkhave … pe … "
msgstr "“So you should truly see … "

msgctxt "sn22.100:4.11"
msgid "evaṃ passaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "Seeing this … "

msgctxt "sn22.100:4.12"
msgid "nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānātī”ti. "
msgstr "They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.100:4.13"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

